Short Description:
Sports Business Ventures (SBV) is a sports brand and career development platform founded by Brian and Ellen Davison. With over 28 years of combined experience in the sports industry, SBV focuses on empowering aspiring and current sports professionals through various services, including media, community engagement, consulting, networking, mentorship, and recruitment.

Headquartered in the UK and US, SBV serves a community of over 100,000 members, providing access to job boards, newsletters, workshops, events, and educational courses. The company launched the first universal sports business club, emphasizing authentic relationships and career growth. Key offerings include a mentorship program that connects mentees with industry executives, consulting services for sports brands, and recruiting services in partnership with Careers Launch Talent Group. SBV is dedicated to shaping the future of the sports industry and fostering connections among professionals.

The Jonus Group is a staffing firm that specializes in the insurance industry. It connects skilled professionals with leading clients by focusing on recruitment for various roles in commercial insurance, compliance, accounting, legal, and related fields. The company emphasizes placements in sectors such as property and casualty, auto insurance, employee benefits, and commercial lines, supporting both permanent and full-time positions, often with hybrid work options.

The Jonus Group offers tailored recruitment and staffing services, sourcing candidates for roles like Commercial Lines Account Managers, Compliance Directors, and Risk Advisors. It manages job placements that involve tasks such as compliance risk assessments and client relationship building. The firm serves a diverse range of clients, including established insurance agencies, leading carriers, and independent agencies across multiple locations. Testimonials highlight the company's reliability in quickly scaling teams with high-quality candidates.

The platform connects skilled professionals in fields such as development, marketing, writing, and design with businesses looking for top talent for remote projects. Wiraa has grown from its initial focus on creative professionals in the consumer services sector to a comprehensive network in the professional talent services and information technology industries.

It serves as a free platform for exploring flexible job options across various fields. The company fosters a positive work culture that values teamwork, learning, and work-life balance, making it an appealing choice for software developers, interns, and remote workers.

Parafin is a financial infrastructure company founded in 2020, headquartered in San Francisco, California. It provides platforms such as marketplaces and vertical SaaS with embedded financial products tailored for small business users. Parafin simplifies complex processes like capital markets, underwriting, and compliance, enabling platforms to offer customized financial solutions through a single integration.

The company has experienced rapid growth, serving hundreds of thousands of small businesses and facilitating over $25 billion in offers. Parafin's key products include flexible financing options, spend management tools, and deferred payment solutions. With a dedicated team of around 99 employees, Parafin has secured significant funding and received multiple recognitions in the fintech space.

R2 Global is an IT recruitment and consulting firm that specializes in niche technology talent, particularly in areas such as Workday, CPQ, CRM, Billing, ERP, and Microsoft Dynamics. Established around 2018-2019, the company operates from multiple locations, including Gold River, California, and Miami, Florida, serving clients in the United States, Canada, and Europe. R2 Global emphasizes a transparent and reliable approach, focusing on quality placements to match top talent with various organizations, including public sector entities, private companies, startups, and global enterprises.

The company offers three main service areas: management consulting, technology consulting, and staffing and recruitment. Their management consulting services include project management and strategy development, while technology consulting provides expert solutions for both public and commercial sectors. R2 Global's recruitment services focus on sourcing and placing talent in specialized technology roles, offering full-cycle recruitment, executive search, and relocation support. They are recognized as an official Workday Partner and have a team with over 15 years of experience in technology recruitment.

Puffy is a direct-to-consumer e-commerce company based in North Hollywood, California, founded in 2016. The company specializes in premium sleep products designed to provide a comfortable and innovative sleeping experience. Puffy operates across the U.S. and Canada, focusing on customer satisfaction and high-quality manufacturing. All mattresses are assembled in the USA using CertiPUR-US certified foams, and the company offers free shipping within 1-2 days, a 101-night sleep trial, and lifetime warranties on its mattresses.

Puffy's product lineup includes a range of mattresses, such as the Puffy Original, Puffy Lux Hybrid, and Royal Hybrid, all featuring proprietary Cooling Cloud™ technology for breathability and comfort. In addition to mattresses, Puffy offers adjustable bed bases, bedding, pillows, weighted blankets, and sleep accessories aimed at enhancing sleep wellness. The company emphasizes a hassle-free customer experience with AI-powered support and a commitment to sleep health, making it a popular choice for consumers seeking quality sleep solutions.

Short Description:
Inspira Education is an education technology company based in New York, founded in 2021. It focuses on transforming the college admissions process through human-centered advising, mentorship, and storytelling. The company aims to make the admissions journey more accessible and less confusing for students preparing for higher education.

Inspira Education operates as part of the Inspira Education Group, which includes various technology-driven coaching platforms. The company emphasizes integrity and student voices, utilizing a 3:1 paid-to-pro bono model to support its mission. With a team of Ivy League-educated advisors, Inspira provides personalized guidance tailored to individual student needs. Its interactive platform features individualized counselor matching, AI-driven insights, and a human-centered advising curriculum based on educational theories from Harvard. 

Inspira targets students, families, and tutors looking for personalized academic support, fostering curiosity and creativity to help students create memorable applications.

Short Description:
Feastables Inc. is a global snacking company founded in 2021 by Jimmy Donaldson, known as MrBeast, and Jim Murray, the former president of RXBAR. Headquartered in Chicago, Illinois, the company specializes in chocolate bars and gummies made with simple, plant-based, gluten-free ingredients. Their product lineup includes various chocolate bar flavors, such as the "MrBeast Bar," and gummies, all manufactured in Peru by Machu Picchu Foods SAC.

Feastables is committed to ethical sourcing, focusing on eradicating child labor in cocoa-growing regions. They source 100% Fairtrade certified cocoa and pay farmers a Living Income Reference Price. The company invests in local communities, children's education, and farmer training. Since its launch, Feastables has expanded rapidly, reaching a 9-figure run rate within 14 months and establishing a presence in major retail stores like Walmart, as well as expanding internationally to markets including the UK, Australia, and Canada.

Short Description:
The New York Foundation for the Arts (NYFA) is a nonprofit organization established in 1971 in New York City. It provides resources, guidance, and funding to individual artists and emerging arts organizations. NYFA aims to empower artists across various creative disciplines, focusing on diversity, equity, inclusion, and accessibility. The organization serves approximately 1 million constituents annually through both in-person and virtual initiatives.

NYFA operates four main programs that include grants, training, and sponsorship. It awards between $2 million and $55 million each year through its Artists' Fellowships, supporting nearly 1,000 artists primarily in New York State. The foundation also offers fiscal sponsorship, helping artists and arts organizations manage funding for their projects. Additionally, NYFA provides professional development opportunities, online resources, and advocacy for arts funding and freedom of expression. The organization is committed to addressing systemic marginalization and supports artists nationwide and globally.

CodeSignal is a San Francisco-based skills assessment and development platform founded in 2015. The company focuses on helping organizations and individuals discover, measure, and cultivate technical talent through AI-powered tools for hiring, upskilling, and learning. With a mission to bridge skills gaps in software development, CodeSignal emphasizes objective, data-driven evaluations that move beyond traditional resumes.

The platform offers a range of services, including AI-powered skills assessments, hiring solutions for technical recruiting, and personalized learning experiences through CodeSignal Learn. These tools support both new talent acquisition and ongoing employee development, with recent expansions into soft skills training. CodeSignal has gained recognition for its innovative approach, ranking #2 in Education on Fast Company's World's Most Innovative Companies list in 2025. The company has raised $87.4 million in funding and serves notable clients such as Meta, Google, and Netflix.

TalentAlly is a diversity-focused job board and recruitment platform that connects job seekers from diverse backgrounds with inclusive employers. Originally known as Professional Diversity Network, the company rebranded to reflect its mission of serving all talented individuals. Headquartered in Chicago, Illinois, TalentAlly has approximately 350 employees and was founded in 1999.

The platform offers a range of services for job seekers, including access to job listings, AI-powered virtual interview practice, resume optimization tools, and professional development resources. TalentAlly also hosts over 40 national career fairs annually. For employers, the platform provides job posting services, branded employer profiles, and AI-driven recruitment tools to enhance candidate engagement and streamline the hiring process. With a commitment to bridging the gap between diverse individuals and inclusive companies, TalentAlly aims to facilitate 1 million job placements by 2026.

FACE FOUNDRIÉ® is a facial bar founded in 2019 by licensed esthetician Michele Henry in Edina, Minnesota. The company aims to provide affordable and efficient professional skincare services in a modern boutique setting. It focuses on inclusivity and offers a welcoming environment for relaxation and self-care. With a reported revenue of around $25 million, FACE FOUNDRIÉ has expanded to 48-57 franchised locations across the U.S. and plans to grow to 150 locations by 2027.

The company offers a range of services, including customized facials, lash and brow treatments, and curated retail skincare products. Appointments are designed to be efficient, lasting 20-40 minutes, and memberships are available to encourage repeat visits. FACE FOUNDRIÉ emphasizes customer satisfaction and aims to empower clients to look and feel their best through expert care and accessible pricing.

Givebutter is a leading nonprofit fundraising platform that has facilitated over $300 million in donations for more than a million changemakers globally. Founded in 2016 and headquartered in Wilmington, Delaware, with operations in Austin, Texas, Givebutter offers a completely free, all-in-one fundraising solution based on a transparent tip-or-fee model.

The platform provides a range of tools for fundraising and donor management, including custom donation forms, fundraising campaigns, event management, and donor relationship tracking. It also features a self-service CRM dashboard, email and text messaging campaigns, and a built-in financial hub called Givebutter Wallet, which offers rewards on funds. Givebutter serves a diverse clientele, including nonprofits, schools, sports teams, and faith-based groups, catering to both small organizations and larger enterprises. The company has received recognition as a Great Place to Work and holds a top ranking on G2 for various nonprofit software categories.

K1X, Inc. is a fintech company based in Chicago, Illinois, founded in 2022. The company specializes in AI-powered SaaS solutions that streamline alternative investment tax compliance by automating the digitization and distribution of K-1 forms and related tax data. K1X has raised $35 million in funding and employs between 20-100 people.

K1X positions itself as a leading data distribution platform for tax compliance, serving over 40,000 organizations, including many top institutional investors and accounting firms. Its flagship product, C-TRAC, is designed for tax-exempt organizations, while the K1x Advantage Suite offers advanced solutions for K-1 aggregation and digital packet production. The platform significantly reduces manual processing time and enhances efficiency, achieving impressive growth metrics in annual recurring revenue and net revenue retention.

Moodys Northwest Consulting (Moodys NWC) is a digital transformation and product consulting firm based in Bellevue, Washington. Founded in 2016, the company specializes in product-led services that drive innovation and efficiency through technology solutions. MARS Solutions Group is a staffing and talent solutions provider founded in 2006 and headquartered in Waukesha, Wisconsin. The company specializes in IT talent acquisition, data management consulting, and human capital solutions for Fortune 500 companies, mid-sized firms, and government agencies. As a certified woman and minority-owned business, MARS Solutions Group has grown into a multimillion-dollar enterprise with approximately 126 employees and reported revenue of $14 million.

The company operates through two main divisions: MARS Talent Solutions and MARS Data Solutions. MARS Talent Solutions focuses on talent acquisition, training, and engagement, including a Returnship program for individuals re-entering the workforce. MARS Data Solutions provides consulting services to help organizations monetize their data assets. MARS Solutions Group serves various industries, including IT, engineering, healthcare, and manufacturing, and is recognized for its commitment to diversity and inclusion in the workplace.

Emergent is an AI-powered platform that allows users to build, test, deploy, and host full-stack applications and websites using natural language prompts. Founded by twin brothers Mukund Jha and Madhav Jha, the company operates from San Francisco and Bengaluru. Its mission is to make software creation accessible to non-technical builders, founders, freelancers, and small businesses.

The platform features a vibe-coding system with specialized AI agents for various tasks, including coding, testing, design, and deployment. It offers end-to-end capabilities, such as native authentication, database management, and payment processing through Stripe. Users can deploy simple apps in under 10 minutes and complex ones in under 30, with real-time monitoring and integration options for tools like GitHub and Slack. Emergent has enabled 4,000 users to create 10,000 live apps, showcasing its effectiveness in rapid prototyping and production-ready development.

Short Description:
Soho Square Solutions is a financial services consulting and staffing firm based in New York City, founded in 2008. The company specializes in risk management, compliance, IT audit, cloud migration, and data solutions tailored for banking and investment institutions. With a team of approximately 102 employees, Soho Square Solutions generates an annual revenue of $17.2 million.

The firm offers a range of consulting services, including enterprise-wide risk modeling, compliance frameworks, and regulatory reporting solutions. They work closely with regulatory agencies such as the Federal Reserve and SEC. Additionally, Soho Square Solutions provides technology and digital transformation services, including cloud migration, IT audits, and big data analysis. Their expertise spans various financial sectors, including investment banking, commercial banking, and asset management, serving clients across the US, Canada, and internationally in regions like India, the UK, and the Middle East.

Short Description:
GAC Solutions is a global consulting and technology services firm founded in 2012, with headquarters in Schaumburg, Illinois, and additional offices in Hyderabad, India, and Monterrey, Mexico. The company specializes in digital transformation, IT consulting, managed services, platform engineering, and staffing solutions. GAC Solutions is recognized as a Minority Business Enterprise and employs a diverse workforce, focusing on innovation in safety-critical systems for medical and industrial sectors.

The firm offers a wide range of professional services, including digital transformation strategy, IT consulting, custom software development, and cloud services. GAC Solutions also provides staffing solutions across various sectors, including IT, Life Sciences, and Engineering. Their proprietary TestOps toolkit enhances software testing through robotic test automation. GAC serves clients across the US, Latin America, EMEA, and APAC, including Fortune 500 and mid-sized enterprises, emphasizing quality, diversity initiatives, and social responsibility.

Short Description:
For fifty years, SBH has stood as a pillar of charity and volunteerism in the community. Although the organization itself has grown exponentially since its inception in May 1974, its core values of selflessness and responsibility have never wavered. 

SBH has been dedicated to the caring of those less fortunate. It is the shoulder to cry on, the lifeline, the answer to your calls for help. Countless leaders have been born, friendships formed, and prides restored. Its truisms have become a part of the very fabric of what it means to be part of "the community"; To care for your neighbor as if they are your brother, to give with compassion, discretion and respect, asking for nothing in return. The breadth and depth of our programs and services now reach each and every family and individual. Whether you have been on the giving or receiving line, you have taken part in the building of an agency that you can be proud to call your own. We thank you for all you have done in helping us reach this point and look forward to many more generations of loving kindness.

Short Description:
Swooped is an AI-powered job search platform designed to assist job seekers in creating optimized resumes and cover letters, streamlining applications, and enhancing networking efforts. Founded to address the creators' own job-search challenges, Swooped aims to simplify the process of landing dream jobs for both job seekers and employers.

For job seekers, Swooped offers a range of free and premium AI tools, including an AI Resume Builder that generates ATS-ready resumes, an AI Cover Letter Generator for personalized cover letters, and one-click applications that allow users to apply to multiple roles quickly. The platform also features networking tools to help users connect with industry contacts and aggregates remote job listings for tailored optimizations.

Employers benefit from Swooped's AI tools that assist in crafting effective job ads and identifying top candidates from applicant pools. This dual-sided platform enhances the hiring process, making it a valuable resource for both job seekers and employers.
